This notebook displays back-end code for the underlying the data used in the "what-if" application. Ideally, this application would use ESRI's Javascript API to compile several of these data management steps into a "custom" widget. Given this skill constraint, we created a simple Web Application using ArcGIS AppBuilder that can be used as an interactive wireframe once a front-end assists in future development with this project.¶

Below is a "look-up" table highlightings findings from an Earth Economics' study providing financial estimates for various types of landcover given attributes such as: Aesthetics, Air Pollution, Carbon Sequestration, Disaster Mitigation, Health, Shelter, Waste, and Water. The columns "low" and "high" representing the estimated minimum and maximum value per acre of a given land type.¶

Prior to using the table above to estimate values, we needed to do a pivot of the "valueType" column so that we can append estimates to the Hexbins. We suggest keeping the table in "long" format in the event FoDP is able to manage data in a database system, or desire to do a few things in Tableau with the data. SQL database queries tend to be more efficient with long formatted tables. That said for the purposes of this demonstration we will have the lookup table in wide format.¶

In [3]:
test=pd.pivot_table(EE,index=['Landcover','Agriculture','Riparian','Urban'],
         columns='valueType',
         values='low')
test.reset_index(inplace=True)
test['index1']=test.index
values1=test[['Aesthetic','Air','Carbon Sequestration',
      'Disaster Mitigation','Health','Shelter','Waste','Water']].add_suffix('_low')
values1['index1']=values1.index
test2=pd.pivot_table(EE,index=['Landcover','Agriculture','Riparian','Urban'],
         columns='valueType',
         values='high')
test2.reset_index(inplace=True)
values2=test2[['Aesthetic','Air','Carbon Sequestration',
      'Disaster Mitigation','Health','Shelter','Waste','Water']].add_suffix('_high')
values2['index1']=values2.index
keyTableEE2 = pd.merge(test[['index1','Landcover','Agriculture','Riparian','Urban']],
                       values1)
keyTableEE = pd.merge(keyTableEE2,values2)
del keyTableEE['index1']
keyTableEE

Now were going to merge the Earth Economic values to the Hexbins given their landcover type. From this data step, we will get low and high financial valuations for our attributes of interest with respect to our Hexbins: Aesthetics, Air Pollution, Carbon Sequestration, Disaster Mitigation, Health, Shelter, Waste, and Water.¶

In [4]:
original = pd.read_csv(direct+"OriginalScenario.csv",
                       encoding = "ISO-8859-1",error_bad_lines=False)
original.head()

newOriginal = original[['OBJECTID','GRID_ID','Acres','Latitude','Longitude',
                        'zoneMGT','LC','Agriculture','Riparian','Urban']]
preOrig = pd.merge(newOriginal,keyTableEE, how='left',
                  left_on=['LC','Agriculture','Riparian','Urban'], 
                  right_on=['Landcover','Agriculture','Riparian','Urban'])

preOrig['aestheticLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Aesthetic_low']
preOrig['aestheticHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Aesthetic_high']
preOrig['airLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Air_low']
preOrig['airHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Air_high']
preOrig['carbonLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Carbon Sequestration_low']
preOrig['carbonHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Carbon Sequestration_high']
preOrig['mitigationLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Disaster Mitigation_low']
preOrig['mitigationHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Disaster Mitigation_high']
preOrig['healthLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Health_low']
preOrig['healthHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Health_high']
preOrig['shelterLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Shelter_low']
preOrig['shelterHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Shelter_high']
preOrig['wasteLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Waste_low']
preOrig['wasteHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Waste_high']
preOrig['waterLowTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Water_low']
preOrig['waterHighTotal'] = preOrig['Acres']*preOrig['Water_high']
preOrig['lowTotal'] = preOrig['aestheticLowTotal']+preOrig['airLowTotal']+preOrig['carbonLowTotal']+preOrig['mitigationLowTotal']+preOrig['healthLowTotal']+preOrig['shelterLowTotal']+preOrig['wasteLowTotal']+preOrig['waterLowTotal']
preOrig['highTotal'] = preOrig['aestheticHighTotal']+preOrig['airHighTotal']+preOrig['carbonHighTotal']+preOrig['mitigationHighTotal']+preOrig['healthHighTotal']+preOrig['shelterHighTotal']+preOrig['wasteHighTotal']+preOrig['waterHighTotal']
preOrig.drop(['Aesthetic_low','Aesthetic_high','Air_low','Air_high',
              'Carbon Sequestration_low','Carbon Sequestration_high',
              'Disaster Mitigation_low','Disaster Mitigation_high',
              'Health_low','Health_high','Shelter_low','Shelter_high',
              'Waste_low','Waste_high','Water_low','Water_high'], axis = 1)

export_csv = preOrig.to_csv (direct+'originalScenario.csv', index = None, header=True)
preOrig.head()

preScene2['aestheticHighTotal'] = preScene2['Acres']*preScene2['Aesthetic_high']

preScene2['mitigationLowTotal'] = preScene2['Acres']*preScene2['Disaster Mitigation_low']

preScene4['aestheticLowTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Aesthetic_low']
preScene4['aestheticHighTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Aesthetic_high']
preScene4['airLowTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Air_low']
preScene4['airHighTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Air_high']
preScene4['carbonLowTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Carbon Sequestration_low']
preScene4['carbonHighTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Carbon Sequestration_high']
preScene4['mitigationLowTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Disaster Mitigation_low']

preScene4['healthLowTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Health_low']
preScene4['healthHighTotal'] = preScene4['Acres']*preScene4['Health_high']
